Sutherland in the Northern Cape is expected to get the heaviest falls. JOHANNESBURG - Brace yourselves for more cold weather. Officials say the front that’s gripping the country will intensify. READ: Big freeze expected as snow falls in Sutherland Snow is expected to continue over the southern Western Cape, with Sutherland in the Northern Cape expected to get the heaviest falls. The South African Weather Service has issued a warning of "disruptive" snowfall for the area. Snow starts to fall in Sutherland on 23 July 2019 Snow covers a stop sign in Sutherland. Snow is falling in Sutherland. This photo was taken on the outskirts of Sutherland on the way to Fraserburg.